Full many a glorious morning have I seen

Flatter the mountain-tops with sovereign eye, Kissing with golden face the meadows green, Gilding pale streams with heavenly alchemy;

Anon permit the basest clouds to ride

And from the forlorn worlds his visage hide, Stealing unseen to west with this disgrace:

Even so my sun one early morn did shine With all-triumphant splendour on my brow; But out, alack! he was but one hour mine;

The region cloud hath mask'd him from me novw.
